&gt; Page Expired 419

This means that the route `join.store`&#160;is under the `VerifyCsrfToken` middleware that protects your application from Cross-Site Request Forgery attack and the posted form data has no (or invalid) `_token`

All what you need to do is add a CSRF token, also you&#39;re not posting anything so you get a redirect from validation
```
&lt;form method=&quot;post&quot; action=&quot;/test&quot;&gt;
    @csrf
    &lt;input type=&quot;hidden&quot; name=&quot;group_title&quot; value=&quot;{{ $group-&gt;group_title }}&quot;&gt;
    &lt;input type=&quot;submit&quot; value=&quot;Join Group&quot; class=&quot;btn btn-success&quot; /&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;
```
Also you&#39;re not correctly creating the model

### Update: do not redirect unless you create the group
```php
$joined = Join::create([
                 &#39;group_title&#39; =&gt; $request-&gt;get(&#39;group_title&#39;)
          ]);
if ($joined) {
   return redirect(&#39;/join&#39;)-&gt;with(&#39;success&#39;, &#39;Group joined!!&#39;);
}
return response-&gt;json([&#39;status&#39; =&gt; &#39;Failed to create group&#39;]);
```

Another option is to disable the protection for the route in the middleware (this is useful for API tests with Postman)

**DO NOT DO THIS**

```php
&lt;?php

namespace App\Http\Middleware;

use Illuminate\Foundation\Http\Middleware\VerifyCsrfToken as Middleware;

class VerifyCsrfToken extends Middleware
{
    /**
     * Indicates whether the XSRF-TOKEN cookie should be set on the response.
     *
     * @var bool
     */
    protected $addHttpCookie = true;

    /**
     * The URIs that should be excluded from CSRF verification.
     *
     * @var array
     */
    protected $except = [
        &#39;/join/store&#39; // Place the routes you want to exclude here
    ];
}
```

### Note if your Laravel version is below 5.6

use this instead 
```
{{ csrf_field() }}
```

Or manually created the input
```html
&lt;input type=&quot;hidden&quot; name=&quot;_token&quot; value=&quot;{{ csrf_token() }}&quot;&gt;
```

[Learn More](https://laravel.com/docs/csrf)

